            <div class="Facts">
                <h3>What is?</h3>
                <p>  
                    Nasi Liwet is a beloved Indonesian dish originating from the Sundanese region of West Java. 
                    This flavorful rice dish is cooked with coconut milk, shallots, garlic, and a blend of aromatic 
                    spices such as lemongrass, bay leaves, and galangal, imparting it with a rich and fragrant taste. 
                    Often served with various side dishes such as fried chicken, tempeh, or tofu, as well as fresh 
                    vegetables and sambal, Nasi Liwet offers a complete and satisfying meal that tantalizes the taste 
                    buds with its harmonious blend of flavors. Enjoyed during special occasions or as a comforting 
                    everyday meal, Nasi Liwet is a culinary delight that reflects the diverse and vibrant food culture 
                    of Indonesia.
                </p>
